2382 #endif // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
2383 
2384 void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
2385  int num_arguments) {
2386  // All parameters are on the stack. r3 has the return value after call.
2387 
2388  // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
2389  // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
2390  // expectation.
2391  CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
2392 
2393  // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
2394  // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
2395  // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
2396  // smarter.
2397  mov(r3, Operand(num_arguments));
2398  Move(r4, ExternalReference::Create(f));
2399  bool switch_to_central_stack = options().is_wasm;
2400  CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size, switch_to_central_stack));
2401 }
2402 
2403 void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
2404  const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
2405  DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
2406  if (function->nargs >= 0) {
2407  mov(r3, Operand(function->nargs));
2408  }
2409  JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
2410 }
2411 
2412 void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& builtin,
2413  bool builtin_exit_frame) {
2414  Move(r4, builtin);
2415  TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
2416 }
2417 
2418 void MacroAssembler::LoadWeakValue(Register out, Register in,
2419  Label* target_if_cleared) {
2420  CmpS32(in, Operand(kClearedWeakHeapObjectLower32), r0);
2421  beq(target_if_cleared);
2422 
2423  mov(r0, Operand(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
2424  and_(out, in, r0);
2425 }
2426 
2427 void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
2428  Register scratch1,
2429  Register scratch2) {
2430  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
2431  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
2432  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
2433  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
2434  // field.
2435  Move(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
2436  lwz(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
2437  addi(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
2438  stw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
2439  }
2440 }
2441 
2442 void MacroAssembler::EmitDecrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
2443  Register scratch1,
2444  Register scratch2) {
2445  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
2446  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
2447  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
2448  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t dummy_stats_counter_
2449  // field.
2450  Move(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
2451  lwz(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
2452  subi(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
2453  stw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
2454  }
2455 }
2456 
2457 void MacroAssembler::Check(Condition cond, AbortReason reason, CRegister cr) {
2458  Label L;
2459  b(cond, &L, cr);
2460  Abort(reason);
2461  // will not return here
2462  bind(&L);
2463 }
2464 
2465 void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
2466  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2467  if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
2468  RecordComment("Abort message:", SourceLocation{});
2469  RecordComment(GetAbortReason(reason), SourceLocation{});
2470  }
2471 
2472  // Without debug code, save the code size and just trap.
2473  if (!v8_flags.debug_code || v8_flags.trap_on_abort) {
2474  stop();
2475  return;
2476  }
2477 
2478  if (should_abort_hard()) {
2479  // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
2480  FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
2481  mov(r3, Operand(static_cast<int>(reason)));
2482  PrepareCallCFunction(1, 0, r4);
2483  Register dst = ip;
2484  if (!ABI_CALL_VIA_IP) {
2485  dst = r4;
2486  }
2487  Move(dst, ExternalReference::abort_with_reason());
2488  // Use Call directly to avoid any unneeded overhead. The function won't
2489  // return anyway.
2490  Call(dst);
2491  return;
2492  }
2493 
2494  LoadSmiLiteral(r4, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
2495 
2496  {
2497  // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
2498  // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
2499  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
2500  if (root_array_available()) {
2501  // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
2502  // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
2503  // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
2504  // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
2505  LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort, ip);
2506  Call(ip);
2507  } else {
2508  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
2509  }
2510  }
2511  // will not return here
2512 }
2513 
2514 void MacroAssembler::LoadMap(Register destination, Register object) {
2515  LoadTaggedField(destination, FieldMemOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset),
2516  r0);
2517 }
2518 
2519 void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
2520  Register scratch, Label* fbv_undef) {
2521  Label done;
2522 
2523  // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
2524  LoadTaggedField(
2525  dst, FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset), r0);
2526  LoadTaggedField(dst, FieldMemOperand(dst, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset), r0);
2527 
2528  // Check if feedback vector is valid.
2529  LoadTaggedField(scratch, FieldMemOperand(dst, HeapObject::kMapOffset), r0);
2530  LoadU16(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
2531  CmpS32(scratch, Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE), r0);
2532  b(eq, &done);
2533 
2534  // Not valid, load undefined.
2535  LoadRoot(dst, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2536  b(fbv_undef);
2537 
2538  bind(&done);
2539 }

2631 void MacroAssembler::AssertGeneratorObject(Register object) {

2639  LoadMap(map, object);
2640

2644  FIRST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE,

2651 void MacroAssembler::AssertUndefinedOrAllocationSite(Register object,

2665 void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
2666  Register tmp, AbortReason abort_reason) {
2667  if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
2668 
2669  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2670  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp, tmp));
2671  Label ok;
2672 
2673  JumpIfSmi(object, &ok);
2674 
2675  LoadMap(map_tmp, object);
2676  CompareInstanceType(map_tmp, tmp, LAST_NAME_TYPE);
2677  ble(&ok);
2678 
2679  CompareInstanceType(map_tmp, tmp, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE);
2680  bge(&ok);
2681 
2682  CompareRoot(map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
2683  beq(&ok);
2684 
2685  CompareRoot(map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
2686  beq(&ok);
2687 
2688  CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
2689  beq(&ok);
2690 
2691  CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
2692  beq(&ok);
2693 
2694  CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
2695  beq(&ok);
2696 
2697  CompareRoot(object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
2698  beq(&ok);
2699 
2700  Abort(abort_reason);
2701 
2702  bind(&ok);
2703 }

2706 
2707 int MacroAssembler::CalculateStackPassedWords(int num_reg_arguments,
2708  int num_double_arguments) {
2709  int stack_passed_words = 0;
2710  if (num_double_arguments > DoubleRegister::kNumRegisters) {
2711  stack_passed_words +=
2712  2 * (num_double_arguments - DoubleRegister::kNumRegisters);
2713  }
2714  // Up to 8 simple arguments are passed in registers r3..r10.
2715  if (num_reg_arguments > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
2716  stack_passed_words += num_reg_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments;
2717  }
2718  return stack_passed_words;
2719 }
2720 
2721 void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
2722  int num_double_arguments,
2723  Register scratch) {
2724  int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
2725  int stack_passed_arguments =
2726  CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
2727  int stack_space = kNumRequiredStackFrameSlots;
2728 
2729  if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
2730  // Make stack end at alignment and make room for stack arguments
2731  // -- preserving original value of sp.
2732  mr(scratch, sp);
2733  AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(-(stack_passed_arguments + 1) * kSystemPointerSize),
2734  scratch);
2735  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
2736  ClearRightImm(sp, sp,
2737  Operand(base::bits::WhichPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment)));
2738  StoreU64(scratch,
2739  MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
2740  } else {
2741  // Make room for stack arguments
2742  stack_space += stack_passed_arguments;
2743  }
2744 
2745  // Allocate frame with required slots to make ABI work.
2746  li(r0, Operand::Zero());
2747  StoreU64WithUpdate(r0, MemOperand(sp, -stack_space * kSystemPointerSize));
2748 }
2749 
2750 void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
2751  Register scratch) {
2752  PrepareCallCFunction(num_reg_arguments, 0, scratch);
2753 }

2755 void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatParameter(DoubleRegister src) { Move(d1, src); }
2756 
2757 void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatResult(DoubleRegister src) { Move(d1, src); }
2758 
2759 void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatParameters(DoubleRegister src1,
2760  DoubleRegister src2) {
2761  if (src2 == d1) {
2762  DCHECK(src1 != d2);
2763  Move(d2, src2);
2764  Move(d1, src1);
2765  } else {
2766  Move(d1, src1);
2767  Move(d2, src2);
2768  }
2769 }

2771 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function,
2772  int num_reg_arguments,
2773  int num_double_arguments,
2774  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
2775  bool has_function_descriptor) {
2776  Move(ip, function);
2777  return CallCFunction(ip, num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments,
2778  set_isolate_data_slots, has_function_descriptor);
2779 }
2780 
2781 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_reg_arguments,
2782  int num_double_arguments,
2783  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
2784  bool has_function_descriptor) {
2785  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2786  DCHECK_LE(num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
2787  DCHECK(has_frame());
2788 
2789  Label start_call;
2790  Register pc_scratch = r11;
2791  DCHECK(!AreAliased(pc_scratch, function));
2792  LoadPC(pc_scratch);
2793  bind(&start_call);
2794  int start_pc_offset = pc_offset();
2795  // We are going to patch this instruction after emitting
2796  // Call, using a zero offset here as placeholder for now.
2797  // patch_pc_address assumes `addi` is used here to
2798  // add the offset to pc.
2799  addi(pc_scratch, pc_scratch, Operand::Zero());
2800 
2801  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
2802  // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains iterable,
2803  // even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS and C frames.
2804  Register scratch = r8;
2805  Push(scratch);
2806  mflr(scratch);
2807  CHECK(root_array_available());
2808  StoreU64(pc_scratch,
2809  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerPC));
2810  StoreU64(fp,
2811  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
2812  mtlr(scratch);
2813  Pop(scratch);
2814  }
2815 
2816  Register dest = function;
2817  if (ABI_USES_FUNCTION_DESCRIPTORS && has_function_descriptor) {
2818  // AIX/PPC64BE Linux uses a function descriptor. When calling C code be
2819  // aware of this descriptor and pick up values from it
2820  LoadU64(ToRegister(ABI_TOC_REGISTER),
2821  MemOperand(function, kSystemPointerSize));
2822  LoadU64(ip, MemOperand(function, 0));
2823  dest = ip;
2824  } else if (ABI_CALL_VIA_IP) {
2825  // pLinux and Simualtor, not AIX
2826  Move(ip, function);
2827  dest = ip;
2828  }
2829 
2830  int call_pc_offset;
2831  {
2832  ConstantPoolUnavailableScope block_const_pool_scope(this);
2833  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2834  Call(dest);
2835  call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
2836  int offset_since_start_call = SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(&start_call);
2837  // Here we are going to patch the `addi` instruction above to use the
2838  // correct offset.
2839  // LoadPC emits two instructions and pc is the address of its second emitted
2840  // instruction. Add one more to the offset to point to after the Call.
2841  offset_since_start_call += kInstrSize;
2842  patch_pc_address(pc_scratch, start_pc_offset, offset_since_start_call);
2843 
2844  int before_offset = pc_offset();
2845  int stack_passed_arguments =
2846  CalculateStackPassedWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
2847  int stack_space = kNumRequiredStackFrameSlots + stack_passed_arguments;
2848  if (ActivationFrameAlignment() > kSystemPointerSize) {
2849  // Using prefixed load may emit `nop` which then fails the check below.
2850  ld(sp, MemOperand(sp, stack_space * kSystemPointerSize));
2851  } else {
2852  AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(stack_space * kSystemPointerSize), r0);
2853  }
2854  // We assume that the move instruction uses kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall
2855  // bytes. When we patch in the deopt trampoline, we patch it in after the
2856  // move instruction, so that the stack has been restored correctly.
2857  CHECK_EQ(kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall, pc_offset() - before_offset);
2858  }
2859 
2860  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
2861  // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
2862  Register zero_scratch = r0;
2863  mov(zero_scratch, Operand::Zero());
2864 
2865  StoreU64(zero_scratch,
2866  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
2867  }
2868 
2869  return call_pc_offset;
2870 }
2871 
2872 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(ExternalReference function, int num_arguments,
2873  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
2874  bool has_function_descriptor) {
2875  return CallCFunction(function, num_arguments, 0, set_isolate_data_slots,
2876  has_function_descriptor);
2877 }

2879 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_arguments,
2880  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,

2882  return CallCFunction(function, num_arguments, 0, set_isolate_data_slots,
2883  has_function_descriptor);
2884 }

2886 void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(
2887  Register object,
2888  Register scratch, // scratch may be same register as object
2889  int mask, Condition cc, Label* condition_met) {
2890  DCHECK(cc == ne || cc == eq);
2891  DCHECK(scratch != r0);
2892  ClearRightImm(scratch, object, Operand(kPageSizeBits));
2893  LoadU64(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()), r0);
2894 
2895  mov(r0, Operand(mask));
2896  and_(r0, scratch, r0, SetRC);
2897 
2898  if (cc == ne) {
2899  bne(condition_met, cr0);
2900  }
2901  if (cc == eq) {
2902  beq(condition_met, cr0);
2903  }
2904 }

2925 void MacroAssembler::LoadDoubleLiteral(DoubleRegister result,
2926  base::Double value, Register scratch) {
2927  if (V8_EMBEDDED_CONSTANT_POOL_BOOL && is_constant_pool_available() &&
2928  !(scratch == r0 && ConstantPoolAccessIsInOverflow())) {
2929  ConstantPoolEntry::Access access = ConstantPoolAddEntry(value);
2930  if (access == ConstantPoolEntry::OVERFLOWED) {
2931  addis(scratch, kConstantPoolRegister, Operand::Zero());
2932  lfd(result, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
2933  } else {
2934  lfd(result, MemOperand(kConstantPoolRegister, 0));
2935  }
2936  return;
2937  }
2938 
2939  // avoid gcc strict aliasing error using union cast
2940  union {
2941  uint64_t dval;
2942  intptr_t ival;
2943  } litVal;
2944 
2945  litVal.dval = value.AsUint64();
2946 
2947  mov(scratch, Operand(litVal.ival));
2948  mtfprd(result, scratch);
2949 }

3472 #define GenerateMemoryOperation(reg, mem, ri_op, rr_op) \
3473  { \
3474  int64_t offset = mem.offset(); \
3475  \
3476  if (mem.rb() == no_reg) { \
3477  if (!is_int16(offset)) { \
3478  /* cannot use d-form */ \
3479  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3480  mov(scratch, Operand(offset)); \
3481  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3482  } else { \
3483  ri_op(reg, mem); \
3484  } \
3485  } else { \
3486  if (offset == 0) { \
3487  rr_op(reg, mem); \
3488  } else if (is_int16(offset)) { \
3489  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3490  addi(scratch, mem.rb(), Operand(offset)); \
3491  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3492  } else { \
3493  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3494  mov(scratch, Operand(offset)); \
3495  add(scratch, scratch, mem.rb()); \
3496  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3497  } \
3498  } \
3499  }
3500 
3501 #define GenerateMemoryOperationRR(reg, mem, op) \
3502  { \
3503  if (mem.offset() == 0) { \
3504  if (mem.rb() != no_reg) \
3505  op(reg, mem); \
3506  else \
3507  op(reg, MemOperand(r0, mem.ra())); \
3508  } else if (is_int16(mem.offset())) { \
3509  if (mem.rb() != no_reg) \
3510  addi(scratch, mem.rb(), Operand(mem.offset())); \
3511  else \
3512  mov(scratch, Operand(mem.offset())); \
3513  op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3514  } else { \
3515  mov(scratch, Operand(mem.offset())); \
3516  if (mem.rb() != no_reg) add(scratch, scratch, mem.rb()); \
3517  op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3518  } \
3519  }
3520 
3521 #define GenerateMemoryOperationPrefixed(reg, mem, ri_op, rip_op, rr_op) \
3522  { \
3523  int64_t offset = mem.offset(); \
3524  \
3525  if (mem.rb() == no_reg) { \
3526  if (is_int16(offset)) { \
3527  ri_op(reg, mem); \
3528  } else if (is_int34(offset) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_10_PLUS)) { \
3529  rip_op(reg, mem); \
3530  } else { \
3531  /* cannot use d-form */ \
3532  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3533  mov(scratch, Operand(offset)); \
3534  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3535  } \
3536  } else { \
3537  if (offset == 0) { \
3538  rr_op(reg, mem); \
3539  } else if (is_int16(offset)) { \
3540  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3541  addi(scratch, mem.rb(), Operand(offset)); \
3542  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3543  } else { \
3544  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3545  mov(scratch, Operand(offset)); \
3546  add(scratch, scratch, mem.rb()); \
3547  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3548  } \
3549  } \
3550  }
3551 
3552 #define GenerateMemoryOperationWithAlign(reg, mem, ri_op, rr_op) \
3553  { \
3554  int64_t offset = mem.offset(); \
3555  int misaligned = (offset & 3); \
3556  \
3557  if (mem.rb() == no_reg) { \
3558  if (!is_int16(offset) || misaligned) { \
3559  /* cannot use d-form */ \
3560  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3561  mov(scratch, Operand(offset)); \
3562  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3563  } else { \
3564  ri_op(reg, mem); \
3565  } \
3566  } else { \
3567  if (offset == 0) { \
3568  rr_op(reg, mem); \
3569  } else if (is_int16(offset)) { \
3570  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3571  addi(scratch, mem.rb(), Operand(offset)); \
3572  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3573  } else { \
3574  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3575  mov(scratch, Operand(offset)); \
3576  add(scratch, scratch, mem.rb()); \
3577  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3578  } \
3579  } \
3580  }
3581 
3582 #define GenerateMemoryOperationWithAlignPrefixed(reg, mem, ri_op, rip_op, \
3583  rr_op) \
3584  { \
3585  int64_t offset = mem.offset(); \
3586  int misaligned = (offset & 3); \
3587  \
3588  if (mem.rb() == no_reg) { \
3589  if (is_int16(offset) && !misaligned) { \
3590  ri_op(reg, mem); \
3591  } else if (is_int34(offset) && CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_10_PLUS)) { \
3592  rip_op(reg, mem); \
3593  } else { \
3594  /* cannot use d-form */ \
3595  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3596  mov(scratch, Operand(offset)); \
3597  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3598  } \
3599  } else { \
3600  if (offset == 0) { \
3601  rr_op(reg, mem); \
3602  } else if (is_int16(offset)) { \
3603  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3604  addi(scratch, mem.rb(), Operand(offset)); \
3605  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3606  } else { \
3607  CHECK_NE(scratch, no_reg); \
3608  mov(scratch, Operand(offset)); \
3609  add(scratch, scratch, mem.rb()); \
3610  rr_op(reg, MemOperand(mem.ra(), scratch)); \
3611  } \
3612  } \
3613  }
3614

3962 #define EMIT_SIMD_ALL_TRUE(name, op) \
3963  void MacroAssembler::name(Register dst, Simd128Register src, \
3964  Register scratch1, Register scratch2, \
3965  Simd128Register scratch3) { \
3966  constexpr uint8_t fxm = 0x2; /* field mask. */ \
3967  constexpr int bit_number = 24; \
3968  li(scratch1, Operand(0)); \
3969  li(scratch2, Operand(1)); \
3970  /* Check if all lanes > 0, if not then return false.*/ \
3971  vxor(scratch3, scratch3, scratch3); \
3972  mtcrf(scratch1, fxm); /* Clear cr6.*/ \
3973  op(scratch3, src, scratch3, SetRC); \
3974  isel(dst, scratch2, scratch1, bit_number); \
3975  }
3976 SIMD_ALL_TRUE_LIST(EMIT_SIMD_ALL_TRUE)
3977 #undef EMIT_SIMD_ALL_TRUE
3978 #undef SIMD_ALL_TRUE_LIST

3985 #define EMIT_SIMD_BITMASK(name, op, indicies) \
3986  void MacroAssembler::name(Register dst, Simd128Register src, \
3987  Register scratch1, Simd128Register scratch2) { \
3988  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_10_PLUS)) { \
3989  op(dst, src); \
3990  } else { \
3991  mov(scratch1, Operand(indicies)); /* Select 0 for the high bits. */ \
3992  mtvsrd(scratch2, scratch1); \
3993  vbpermq(scratch2, src, scratch2); \
3994  vextractub(scratch2, scratch2, Operand(6)); \
3995  mfvsrd(dst, scratch2); \
3996  } \
3997  }

4008 #define EMIT_SIMD_QFM(name, op) \
4009  void MacroAssembler::name(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1, \
4010  Simd128Register src2, Simd128Register src3, \
4011  Simd128Register scratch) { \
4012  Simd128Register dest = dst; \
4013  if (dst != src1) { \
4014  vor(scratch, src1, src1); \
4015  dest = scratch; \
4016  } \
4017  op(dest, src2, src3); \
4018  if (dest != dst) { \
4019  vor(dst, dest, dest); \
4020  } \
4021  }

4026 void MacroAssembler::I64x2ExtMulLowI32x4S(Simd128Register dst,
4027  Simd128Register src1,
4028  Simd128Register src2,
4029  Simd128Register scratch) {
4030  constexpr int lane_width_in_bytes = 8;
4031  EXT_MUL(scratch, dst, vmulesw, vmulosw)
4032  vextractd(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 * lane_width_in_bytes));
4033  vinsertd(dst, scratch, Operand(0));
4034 }

4067 void MacroAssembler::LoadSimd128LE(Simd128Register dst, const MemOperand& mem,
4068  Register scratch) {
4069 #ifdef V8_TARGET_BIG_ENDIAN
4070  LoadSimd128(dst, mem, scratch);

4189 void MacroAssembler::F64x2ReplaceLane(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
4190  DoubleRegister src2, uint8_t imm_lane_idx,
4191  Register scratch1,
4192  Simd128Register scratch2) {
4193  constexpr int lane_width_in_bytes = 8;
4194  if (src1 != dst) {
4195  vor(dst, src1, src1);
4196  }
4197  MovDoubleToInt64(scratch1, src2);
4198  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_10_PLUS)) {
4199  vinsd(dst, scratch1, Operand((1 - imm_lane_idx) * lane_width_in_bytes));
4200  } else {
4201  mtvsrd(scratch2, scratch1);
4202  vinsertd(dst, scratch2, Operand((1 - imm_lane_idx) * lane_width_in_bytes));
4203  }
4204 }

4275 void MacroAssembler::I64x2Mul(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
4276  Simd128Register src2, Register scratch1,
4277  Register scratch2, Register scratch3,
4278  Simd128Register scratch4) {
4279  constexpr int lane_width_in_bytes = 8;
4280  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_10_PLUS)) {
4281  vmulld(dst, src1, src2);
4282  } else {
4283  Register scratch_1 = scratch1;
4284  Register scratch_2 = scratch2;
4285  for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++) {
4286  if (i > 0) {
4287  vextractd(scratch4, src1, Operand(1 * lane_width_in_bytes));
4288  vextractd(dst, src2, Operand(1 * lane_width_in_bytes));
4289  src1 = scratch4;
4290  src2 = dst;
4291  }
4292  mfvsrd(scratch_1, src1);
4293  mfvsrd(scratch_2, src2);
4294  mulld(scratch_1, scratch_1, scratch_2);
4295  scratch_1 = scratch2;
4296  scratch_2 = scratch3;
4297  }
4298  mtvsrdd(dst, scratch1, scratch2);
4299  }
4300 }
4301 
4302 void MacroAssembler::I16x8Mul(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
4303  Simd128Register src2) {
4304  vxor(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
4305  vmladduhm(dst, src1, src2, kSimd128RegZero);
4306 }

4308 #define F64X2_MIN_MAX_NAN(result) \
4309  xvcmpeqdp(scratch2, src1, src1); \
4310  vsel(result, src1, result, scratch2); \
4311  xvcmpeqdp(scratch2, src2, src2); \
4312  vsel(dst, src2, result, scratch2); \
4313  /* Use xvmindp to turn any selected SNANs to QNANs. */ \
4314  xvmindp(dst, dst, dst);
4315 void MacroAssembler::F64x2Min(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
4316  Simd128Register src2, Simd128Register scratch1,
4317  Simd128Register scratch2) {
4318  xvmindp(scratch1, src1, src2);
4319  // We need to check if an input is NAN and preserve it.
4320  F64X2_MIN_MAX_NAN(scratch1)
4321 }

4670 void MacroAssembler::I8x16Swizzle(Simd128Register dst, Simd128Register src1,
4671  Simd128Register src2,
4672  Simd128Register scratch) {
4673  // Saturate the indices to 5 bits. Input indices more than 31 should
4674  // return 0.
4675  xxspltib(scratch, Operand(31));
4676  vminub(scratch, src2, scratch);
4677  // Input needs to be reversed.
4678  xxbrq(dst, src1);
4679  vxor(kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero, kSimd128RegZero);
4680  vperm(dst, dst, kSimd128RegZero, scratch);
4681 }

4697  add(dst, scratch2, scratch1);

4955 void MacroAssembler::V128AnyTrue(Register dst, Simd128Register src,
4956  Register scratch1, Register scratch2,
4957  Simd128Register scratch3) {
4958  constexpr uint8_t fxm = 0x2; // field mask.
4959  constexpr int bit_number = 24;
4960  li(scratch1, Operand(0));
4961  li(scratch2, Operand(1));
4962  // Check if both lanes are 0, if so then return false.
4963  vxor(scratch3, scratch3, scratch3);
4964  mtcrf(scratch1, fxm); // Clear cr6.
4965  vcmpequd(scratch3, src, scratch3, SetRC);
4966  isel(dst, scratch1, scratch2, bit_number);
4967 }

4985 Register GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register reg3,
4986  Register reg4, Register reg5,
4987  Register reg6) {
4988  RegList regs = {reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4, reg5, reg6};
4989 
4990  const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
4991  for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
4992  int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
4993  Register candidate = Register::from_code(code);
4994  if (regs.has(candidate)) continue;
4995  return candidate;
4996  }
4997  UNREACHABLE();
4998 }

5000 void MacroAssembler::SwapP(Register src, Register dst, Register scratch) {
5001  if (src == dst) return;
5002  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst, scratch));
5003  mr(scratch, src);
5004  mr(src, dst);
5005  mr(dst, scratch);
5006 }
5007 
5008 void MacroAssembler::SwapP(Register src, MemOperand dst, Register scratch) {
5009  if (dst.ra() != r0 && dst.ra().is_valid())
5010  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst.ra(), scratch));
5011  if (dst.rb() != r0 && dst.rb().is_valid())
5012  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, dst.rb(), scratch));
5013  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src, scratch));
5014  mr(scratch, src);
5015  LoadU64(src, dst, r0);
5016  StoreU64(scratch, dst, r0);
5017 }
5018 
5019 void MacroAssembler::SwapP(MemOperand src, MemOperand dst, Register scratch_0,
5020  Register scratch_1) {
5021  if (src.ra() != r0 && src.ra().is_valid())
5022  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src.ra(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
5023  if (src.rb() != r0 && src.rb().is_valid())
5024  DCHECK(!AreAliased(src.rb(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
5025  if (dst.ra() != r0 && dst.ra().is_valid())
5026  DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst.ra(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
5027  if (dst.rb() != r0 && dst.rb().is_valid())
5028  DCHECK(!AreAliased(dst.rb(), scratch_0, scratch_1));
5029  DCHECK(!AreAliased(scratch_0, scratch_1));
5030  if (is_int16(src.offset()) || is_int16(dst.offset())) {
5031  if (!is_int16(src.offset())) {
5032  // swap operand
5033  MemOperand temp = src;
5034  src = dst;
5035  dst = temp;
5036  }
5037  LoadU64(scratch_1, dst, scratch_0);
5038  LoadU64(scratch_0, src);
5039  StoreU64(scratch_1, src);
5040  StoreU64(scratch_0, dst, scratch_1);
5041  } else {
5042  LoadU64(scratch_1, dst, scratch_0);
5043  push(scratch_1);
5044  LoadU64(scratch_0, src, scratch_1);
5045  StoreU64(scratch_0, dst, scratch_1);
5046  pop(scratch_1);
5047  StoreU64(scratch_1, src, scratch_0);
5048  }
5049 }

5131 void MacroAssembler::ByteReverseU16(Register dst, Register val,
5132  Register scratch) {
5133  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_10_PLUS)) {
5134  brh(dst, val);
5135  ZeroExtHalfWord(dst, dst);
5136  return;
5137  }
5138  rlwinm(scratch, val, 8, 16, 23);
5139  rlwinm(dst, val, 24, 24, 31);
5140  orx(dst, scratch, dst);
5141  ZeroExtHalfWord(dst, dst);
5142 }
5143 
5144 void MacroAssembler::ByteReverseU32(Register dst, Register val,
5145  Register scratch) {
5146  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_10_PLUS)) {
5147  brw(dst, val);
5148  ZeroExtWord32(dst, dst);
5149  return;
5150  }
5151  rotlwi(scratch, val, 8);
5152  rlwimi(scratch, val, 24, 0, 7);
5153  rlwimi(scratch, val, 24, 16, 23);
5154  ZeroExtWord32(dst, scratch);
5155 }
5156 
5157 void MacroAssembler::ByteReverseU64(Register dst, Register val, Register) {
5158  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_10_PLUS)) {
5159  brd(dst, val);
5160  return;
5161  }
5162  subi(sp, sp, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5163  std(val, MemOperand(sp));
5164  ldbrx(dst, MemOperand(r0, sp));
5165  addi(sp, sp, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5166 }

5178 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(Register builtin_index,
5179  Register target) {
5180  static_assert(kSystemPointerSize == 8);
5181  static_assert(kSmiTagSize == 1);
5182  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5183 
5184  // The builtin_index register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
5185  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
5186  ShiftRightS64(target, builtin_index,
5187  Operand(kSmiShift - kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
5188  } else {
5189  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
5190  ShiftLeftU64(target, builtin_index,
5191  Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2 - kSmiShift));
5192  }
5193  AddS64(target, target, Operand(IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset()));
5194  LoadU64(target, MemOperand(kRootRegister, target));
5195 }
5196

5201 }

5218 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(Register destination,
5219  Register dispatch_handle,
5220  Register scratch) {
5221  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, dispatch_handle, scratch));
5222  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);

5228  ShiftRightU64(index, dispatch_handle, Operand(kJSDispatchHandleShift));
5229  ShiftLeftU64(index, index, Operand(kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2));
5230  AddS64(scratch, scratch, index);

5232 }

5263 void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
5264  uint16_t argument_count, Register scratch) {
5265  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
5266 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5267  Register dispatch_handle = r0;
5268  LoadU32(dispatch_handle,
5269  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
5270  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, ip);
5271  Call(code);
5272 #elif V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5273  // When the sandbox is enabled, we can directly fetch the entrypoint pointer
5274  // from the code pointer table instead of going through the Code object. In
5275  // this way, we avoid one memory load on this code path.
5276  LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(
5277  code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset), scratch);
5278  Call(code);
5279 #else
5280  LoadTaggedField(
5281  code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset), scratch);
5282  CallCodeObject(code);
5283 #endif
5284 }
5285 
5286 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5287 void MacroAssembler::CallJSDispatchEntry(JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
5288  uint16_t argument_count) {
5289  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
5290  Register dispatch_handle_reg = r0;
5291  Register scratch = ip;
5292  mov(dispatch_handle_reg,
5293  Operand(dispatch_handle.value(), RelocInfo::JS_DISPATCH_HANDLE));
5294  // WARNING: This entrypoint load is only safe because we are storing a
5295  // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle in the movl above (thus keeping the
5296  // dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not compactable
5297  // (thus meaning that the calculation in the entrypoint load is not
5298  // invalidated by a compaction).
5299  // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
5300  static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
5301  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle_reg, scratch);
5302  CHECK_EQ(argument_count,
5303  IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->GetParameterCount(
5304  dispatch_handle));
5305  Call(code);
5306 }
5307 #endif
5308 
5309 void MacroAssembler::JumpJSFunction(Register function_object, Register scratch,
5310  JumpMode jump_mode) {
5311  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
5312 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5313  Register dispatch_handle = r0;
5314  LoadU32(dispatch_handle,
5315  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
5316  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, ip);
5317  Jump(code);
5318 #elif V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5319  // When the sandbox is enabled, we can directly fetch the entrypoint pointer
5320  // from the code pointer table instead of going through the Code object. In
5321  // this way, we avoid one memory load on this code path.
5322  LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(
5323  code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset), scratch);
5324  DCHECK_EQ(jump_mode, JumpMode::kJump);
5325  DCHECK_EQ(code, r5);
5326  Jump(code);
5327 #else
5328  LoadTaggedField(
5329  code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset), scratch);
5330  JumpCodeObject(code, jump_mode);
5331 #endif
5332 }

5336 void MacroAssembler::ResolveWasmCodePointer(Register target) {
5337  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5338  static_assert(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
5339  ExternalReference global_jump_table =
5340  ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
5341  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5342  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5343  Move(scratch, global_jump_table);
5344  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == kSystemPointerSize);
5345  ShiftLeftU32(target, target, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
5346  LoadU64(target, MemOperand(scratch, target));
5347 }
5348 
5349 void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointer(Register target,
5350  CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
5351  ResolveWasmCodePointer(target);
5352  if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
5353  Jump(target);
5354  } else {
5355  Call(target);
5356  }
5357 }

5366 void MacroAssembler::StoreReturnAddressAndCall(Register target) {
5367  // This generates the final instruction sequence for calls to C functions
5368  // once an exit frame has been constructed.
5369  //
5370  // Note that this assumes the caller code (i.e. the InstructionStream object
5371  // currently being generated) is immovable or that the callee function cannot
5372  // trigger GC, since the callee function will return to it.
5373 
5374  static constexpr int after_call_offset = 5 * kInstrSize;
5375  Label start_call;
5376  Register dest = target;
5377 
5378  if (ABI_USES_FUNCTION_DESCRIPTORS) {
5379  // AIX/PPC64BE Linux uses a function descriptor. When calling C code be
5380  // aware of this descriptor and pick up values from it
5381  LoadU64(ToRegister(ABI_TOC_REGISTER),
5382  MemOperand(target, kSystemPointerSize));
5383  LoadU64(ip, MemOperand(target, 0));
5384  dest = ip;
5385  } else if (ABI_CALL_VIA_IP && dest != ip) {
5386  Move(ip, target);
5387  dest = ip;
5388  }
5389 
5390  LoadPC(r7);
5391  bind(&start_call);
5392  addi(r7, r7, Operand(after_call_offset));
5393  StoreU64(r7, MemOperand(sp, kStackFrameExtraParamSlot * kSystemPointerSize));
5394  Call(dest);
5395 
5396  DCHECK_EQ(after_call_offset - kInstrSize,
5397  SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(&start_call));
5398 }
5399 
5400 // Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
5401 // jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
5402 // to:
5403 // 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
5404 // the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
5405 // 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
5406 // 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
5407 //
5408 // Note: With leaptiering we simply assert the code is not deoptimized.
5409 void MacroAssembler::BailoutIfDeoptimized() {
5410  int offset = InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
5411  if (v8_flags.debug_code || !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL) {
5412  LoadTaggedField(r11, MemOperand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset),
5413  r0);
5414  LoadU32(r11, FieldMemOperand(r11, Code::kFlagsOffset), r0);
5415  TestBit(r11, Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit);
5416  }
5417 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5418  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5419  Assert(to_condition(kZero), AbortReason::kInvalidDeoptimizedCode);
5420  }
5421 #else
5422  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCompileLazyDeoptimizedCode, ne, cr0);
5423 #endif
5424 }
5425 
5426 void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
5427  DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
5428  Label*) {
5429  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5430  CHECK_LE(target, Builtins::kLastTier0);
5431  LoadU64(ip, MemOperand(kRootRegister,
5432  IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(target)));
5433  Call(ip);
5434  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
5435  (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy) ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
5436  : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
5437 }

5466 #define COUNT_TRAILING_ZEROES_SLOW(max_count, scratch1, scratch2) \
5467  Label loop, done; \
5468  li(scratch1, Operand(max_count)); \
5469  mtctr(scratch1); \
5470  mr(scratch1, src); \
5471  li(dst, Operand::Zero()); \
5472  bind(&loop); /* while ((src & 1) == 0) */ \
5473  andi(scratch2, scratch1, Operand(1)); \
5474  bne(&done, cr0); \
5475  srdi(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(1)); /* src >>= 1;*/ \
5476  addi(dst, dst, Operand(1)); /* dst++ */ \
5477  bdnz(&loop); \
5478  bind(&done);
5479 void MacroAssembler::CountTrailingZerosU32(Register dst, Register src,
5480  Register scratch1, Register scratch2,
5481  RCBit r) {
5482  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_9_PLUS)) {
5483  cnttzw(dst, src, r);
5484  } else {
5485  COUNT_TRAILING_ZEROES_SLOW(32, scratch1, scratch2);
5486  }
5487 }
5488 
5489 void MacroAssembler::CountTrailingZerosU64(Register dst, Register src,
5490  Register scratch1, Register scratch2,
5491  RCBit r) {
5492  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(PPC_9_PLUS)) {
5493  cnttzd(dst, src, r);
5494  } else {
5495  COUNT_TRAILING_ZEROES_SLOW(64, scratch1, scratch2);
5496  }
5497 }
5498 #undef COUNT_TRAILING_ZEROES_SLOW

5500 void MacroAssembler::ClearByteU64(Register dst, int byte_idx) {
5501  CHECK(0 <= byte_idx && byte_idx <= 7);
5502  int shift = byte_idx*8;
5503  rldicl(dst, dst, shift, 8);
5504  rldicl(dst, dst, 64-shift, 0);
5505 }

5507 void MacroAssembler::ReverseBitsU64(Register dst, Register src,
5508  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
5509  ByteReverseU64(dst, src);
5510  for (int i = 0; i < 8; i++) {
5511  ReverseBitsInSingleByteU64(dst, dst, scratch1, scratch2, i);
5512  }
5513 }

5515 void MacroAssembler::ReverseBitsU32(Register dst, Register src,
5516  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
5517  ByteReverseU32(dst, src, scratch1);
5518  for (int i = 4; i < 8; i++) {
5519  ReverseBitsInSingleByteU64(dst, dst, scratch1, scratch2, i);
5520  }
5521 }
5522 
5523 // byte_idx=7 refers to least significant byte
5524 void MacroAssembler::ReverseBitsInSingleByteU64(Register dst, Register src,
5525  Register scratch1,
5526  Register scratch2,
5527  int byte_idx) {
5528  CHECK(0 <= byte_idx && byte_idx <= 7);
5529  int j = byte_idx;
5530  // zero all bits of scratch1
5531  li(scratch2, Operand(0));
5532  for (int i = 0; i <= 7; i++) {
5533  // zero all bits of scratch1
5534  li(scratch1, Operand(0));
5535  // move bit (j+1)*8-i-1 of src to bit j*8+i of scratch1, erase bits
5536  // (j*8+i+1):end of scratch1
5537  int shift = 7 - (2*i);
5538  if (shift < 0) shift += 64;
5539  rldicr(scratch1, src, shift, j*8+i);
5540  // erase bits start:(j*8-1+i) of scratch1 (inclusive)
5541  rldicl(scratch1, scratch1, 0, j*8+i);
5542  // scratch2 = scratch2|scratch1
5543  orx(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
5544  }
5545  // clear jth byte of dst and insert jth byte of scratch2
5546  ClearByteU64(dst, j);
5547  orx(dst, dst, scratch2);
5548 }
5549 
5550 // Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
5551 // from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
5552 // and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
5553 // (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
5554 // (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
5555 // allocated for the fast call).
5556 void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
5557  Register function_address,
5558  ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
5559  int slots_to_drop_on_return,
5560  MemOperand* argc_operand,
5561  MemOperand return_value_operand) {
5562  using ER = ExternalReference;
5563 
5564  Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
5565  MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5566  ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
5567  MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5568  ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
5569  MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5570  ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
5571 
5572  // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback.
5573  Register return_value = r3;
5574  Register scratch = ip;
5575  Register scratch2 = r0;
5576 
5577  // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
5578  // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
5579  // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
5580  Register prev_next_address_reg = r14;
5581  Register prev_limit_reg = r15;
5582  Register prev_level_reg = r16;
5583 
5584  // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
5585  // this function must not corrupt them (return_value overlaps with
5586  // kCArgRegs[0] but that's ok because we start using it only after the C
5587  // call).
5588  DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
5589  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
5590  // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
5591  // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
5592  // fine).
5593  DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
5594  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
5595  DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
5596  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
5597  {
5598  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
5599  "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
5600  __ LoadU64(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
5601  __ LoadU64(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
5602  __ lwz(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
5603  __ addi(scratch, prev_level_reg, Operand(1));
5604  __ stw(scratch, level_mem_op);
5605  }
5606 
5607  Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
5608  if (with_profiling) {
5609  __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
5610  __ lbz(scratch,
5611  __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode));
5612  __ cmpi(scratch, Operand::Zero());
5613  __ bne(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
5614 #ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
5615  __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
5616  __ Move(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
5617  __ lwz(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
5618  __ cmpi(scratch, Operand::Zero());
5619  __ bne(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
5620 #endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
5621  }
5622 
5623  __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
5624  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address);
5625  __ bind(&done_api_call);
5626 
5627  Label propagate_exception;
5628  Label delete_allocated_handles;
5629  Label leave_exit_frame;
5630 
5631  // load value from ReturnValue
5632  __ RecordComment("Load the value from ReturnValue");
5633  __ LoadU64(r3, return_value_operand);
5634 
5635  {
5636  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
5637  masm,
5638  "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
5639  "Restore previous handle scope.");
5640  __ StoreU64(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
5641  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
5642  __ lwz(scratch, level_mem_op);
5643  __ subi(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
5644  __ CmpS64(scratch, prev_level_reg);
5645  __ Check(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedLevelAfterReturnFromApiCall);
5646  }
5647  __ stw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
5648  __ LoadU64(scratch, limit_mem_op);
5649  __ CmpS64(scratch, prev_limit_reg);
5650  __ bne(&delete_allocated_handles);
5651  }
5652 
5653  __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
5654  __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
5655  Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
5656  if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
5657  // Load the number of stack slots to drop before LeaveExitFrame modifies sp.
5658  __ LoadU64(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
5659  }
5660  __ LeaveExitFrame(scratch);
5661 
5662  {
5663  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
5664  "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
5665  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
5666  __ LoadU64(scratch2, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5667  ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg));
5668  __ CmpS64(scratch, scratch2);
5669  __ bne(&propagate_exception);
5670  }
5671 
5672  __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch, scratch2,
5673  AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
5674 
5675  if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
5676  DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
5677  __ AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
5678 
5679  } else {
5680  // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
5681  __ AddS64(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
5682  __ ShiftLeftU64(r0, argc_reg, Operand(kSystemPointerSizeLog2));
5683  __ AddS64(sp, sp, r0);
5684  }
5685 
5686  __ blr();
5687 
5688  if (with_profiling) {
5689  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via the thunk.");
5690  __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
5691  // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback function.
5692  if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
5693  MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
5694  IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
5695  __ StoreU64(thunk_arg, thunk_arg_mem_op);
5696  }
5697  __ Move(scratch, thunk_ref);
5698  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(scratch);
5699  __ b(&done_api_call);
5700  }
5701 
5702  __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
5703  __ bind(&propagate_exception);
5704  __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
5705 
5706  {
5707  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
5708  masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
5709  __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
5710  __ StoreU64(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
5711  // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
5712  Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
5713  __ mr(saved_result, return_value);
5714  __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, scratch);
5715  __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address());
5716  __ CallCFunction(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions(), 1);
5717  __ mr(return_value, saved_result);
5718  __ b(&leave_exit_frame);
5719  }
5720 }
5721 
5722 } // namespace internal
5723 } // namespace v8
5724 
5725 #undef __
5726 
5727 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_PPC64
__
#define __
